Form.Description: NIH TB Picture Sequence Memory Age 3+

Element.Description: NIH Toolbox Picture Sequence Memory Test

Resource.Description: NIH Toolbox Picture Sequence Memory Test

Element.Description:
Say: Now we are going to play a memory game; but first I am going to teach you how to move the pictures on this screen. Click PLAY.

Say: Here you see some pictures in a yellow box. I want to show you how to move the pictures to the gray boxes. You can move pictures from this yellow box (point) to the gray boxes down here (point), like this. Click on the picture (cutting flowers) in the yellow box; then click on the gray box you want to move it to (first gray box). Now you try with this picture (vase with flowers). Repeat up to a total of 4 times.

Then, say: You can also move pictures from the gray boxes (point) back to the yellow box (point), like this (move cutting flowers to yellow box). Now you move the other picture back to the yellow box (point). Repeat up to a total of 4 times.

Resource.Description:

Then, say: You can also move pictures from the gray boxes (point) back to the yellow box (point), like this (move cutting flowers to yellow box). Now you move the other picture back to the yellow box (point). Repeat up to a total of 4 times.

Element.Description:
Next, move vase with flowers to first gray box; say: You can also move the pictures from one gray box to another, like this (click vase with flowers; click second gray box). First, you click on the picture in one gray box. Then, click on the gray box where you want the picture to go. Now you try it; move this picture from here (second gray box) to here (first gray box). Repeat up to a total of 4 times.

When finished, say: Now, we’re going to play the memory game. I will show you some pictures on the computer. I want you to remember them; then, I want you to show them back to me in the same way I showed you. Click NEXT.

Resource.Description:
Next, move vase with flowers to first gray box; say: You can also move the pictures from one gray box to another, like this (click vase with flowers; click second gray box). First, you click on the picture in one gray box. Then, click on the gray box where you want the picture to go. Now you try it; move this picture from here (second gray box) to here (first gray box). Repeat up to a total of 4 times.

When finished, say: Now, we’re going to play the memory game. I will show you some pictures on the computer. I want you to remember them; then, I want you to show them back to me in the same way I showed you. Click NEXT.

Element.Description:
Say. Now, I’m going to show you how to eat ice cream. Click PLAY.

Point to completed sequence; say: That’s how to eat ice cream. Once pictures are scrambled, say: Now, I want you move the pictures to show me how to eat ice cream. I want you to show them back to me in the same way, in the same order that I showed you.

Point to completed sequence; say: That's how to work on the farm. Once pictures are scrambled, say: Now, you move the pictures to show me how to work on the farm. I want you to show them back to me in the same way, in the same order that I showed you.

When child appears finished, ask: Are you finished?

If child says YES or is obviously finished, click NEXT.
